data.message:
It's that time of the year again... to VOTE!
But we're not just talking elections here. That's right - you can vote right here for this year's FCA superlatives!

This year's superlatives range from "MVP of the Year" to "Most Likely to Win the Hunger Games." For each superlative vote for one male and one female. All nominees must be current undergraduate students. 

Vote on the survey monkey link below by Sunday the 27th!

https://www.surveymonkey.com/s/QKKZCPB

data.message:
Want to TRAVEL, LEARN about Fil-Am issues, and make new FRIENDS?

FCA at UMCP is part of a greater network of Filipino student organizations across the East Coast called the Filipino Intercollegiate Networking Dialogue (FIND). Every spring, FIND holds a conference where you can listen to inspirational speakers about Filipino American issues and network with people from other schools.

This year's FIND Conference will be held at the University of Virginia on SATURDAY, APRIL 5. Rides will be provided. 

If you are interested, please register at this link by MONDAY, MARCH 24 for the pre-registration price of $20: http://conference2014.findinc.org/registration/

Also, check out this event page for more info: https://www.facebook.com/events/639224902799363/

data.message:
For this year's PCN, FCA would like your help in showcasing the stories of other Filipino Americans from campus and the greater DMV community.

We are looking for Filipino Americans who are willing to share how they have overcome identity issues whether they have dealt with colorism, immigration problems, being multiracial, sexuality, gender inequality, or any other topic. In turn, their stories will be displayed in a photo gallery the night of PCN. 

Please fill out this form with the following information to put your nominee in the selection pool. We are looking for people of all ages!

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/1QcWFX0SdqGAQ889YB7wROndnLX6a3LPxpOyrxIzcDPs/viewform
data.name: Fil-Am Photo Exhibit Nominee Form
data.caption: docs.google.com
data.description: This year's PCN is focused on multiple generations of Filipino Americans and their experiences in today's society. What is important to note, however, is that the stories expressed on stage are not the only issues surrounding the Filipino American community. For this reason, FCA would like your help...
